css reset:
*, *:before, *:after {padding: 0; margin: 0;}

** when the content doesnt fit in the box we use the overflow propery in the parent:
overflow: auto; --- makes scrollers bottom and right
overflow: hidden - hides the things that doesnt fit. NO scorller
overflow: scroll - adds scorlls also
overflow: visible -- shows the content outside the box 



html elements types:

Inline elements - elements part of text 
example - span,img, button, map, textarea ....

Block elements - take all the space until the end of the page 
and make a new_line above and below them
examples - h1, p, table, section .... most of the elements are blokck!!!

Inline-Block elements - to change the property of an element to dosplay-Block

** to change the position of a pic and the text should be around it, not after it:
float: right, left ... 

** to clear a p tag with css:
p::after { content: ''; clear: both;} also we can add dosplay: block
for the img we can add -- padding 1em

//PADDING
** padding: up, right,bottom, left --> padding: 1em 1em 1em 1em
** padding [top & bottom] [left & right]
** padding-bolck: [top & bottom]
** padding-inline: [left & right]
** padding: 0 --> no padding
** padding-inline: 1em --> for inline elements, padding-block can also be used

//MARGIN
** margin: up, right,bottom, left --> padding: 1em 1em 1em 1em
** margin [top & bottom] [left & right]
** margin-bolck: [top & bottom]
** margin-inline: [left & right]
** margin: 0 --> no margin

for inline itelms to be used as block intem in the line:
** display: inline-block

// properties for block elements:
width and height can be also with the % --> 50%
width, height, can be used with max or min height, width to specify the max size 
with max-height and max width - the max dimensions if there is a content in the element.
if there is less or no content - it shrinks down

** padding - adding a space between the content and the border of the element.
space IN the element itself ... inner space
** margin - adds a space AFTER the border to the adjecent elements or end of space in browser
outer space b/n the element and other elements

** border: border 1px sodid (dashed) colour;
borders can be: solid, dashed, dotted, double, groove, ridge, inset, outset, none.





